PHUN since there are some questions about a dual token structure Ill heres my earlier reply There are prevailing economic theories that say you cant have a single token economy whereby the coin in use is both a store of value and a medium of exchange A dual token structure can go a long way to address this inherent conflict but it also addresses the inherent problems the SEC has created with a lack of clear regulatory guidance For example the SEC would have blockchain companies qualify a Reg A in order to get crypto into the hands of unaccredited investors but they have shown unwilling to take this strategy seriously However even if they did a company would be limited to up to 50M per 12 months which makes it commercially unfeasible for any large company We will continue to work with the SEC to follow all existing securities regulations in the US but we are a global company so we must move forward in other markets like Asia where blockchain is better understood
